<h1>Vinyl Videos</h1>
<h2>Summary</h2>
<p>
  In this project I set out to add a visual component to my record collection. Specifically, I put together 
  a music video file and added lyric subtitles that sync up with the music when played on vinyl. To watch the video while 
  listening to the record, I added the video file to a Raspberry Pi and hooked the Pi up to a video projector, making sure to play 
  the video in time with the needle on the record. The result is a karaoke-style music video projected onto the wall with subtitles 
  displayed in sync with the music on the record.
</p>
